    {
      "id": "18e4750c-f3ba-8088-8f18-c0b8f037af40",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "KT is a method that aims to model students’ ever-evolving knowledge during skill acquisiton. For that, the authors empirically evaluate tyheir hypothetical model using a tool called APT. The model estimates the probability of the student having learned each of the rules necessary for the ideal model, which allows tutors to present exercises that foster the mastery of specific rules. ",
